"We've broken our hearts, and in 2014 we voted for Zokovi, hoping that he will fulfil our wishes and restore justice."
In fact, only two months after Zokovi took office in October, Pania had the worst nightmare ever.
On 7 December 2014, in front of the bonfire, 11 children at Enarotali sang a Christmas hymn, and two Indonesian soldiers came out on a motorcycle.
The scared kids told them to turn on the headlights.
According to the local priest, Yavet Tebba, one of the soldiers was dissatisfied with their tone and returned with four soldiers.
