The Chief Inspector of Papua Police, Yuje Mende, told journalists that his subordinates were merely “protected” police stations because they had been attacked.
In 2015 Papua Police spokesman, Puggio Sulistio, said, “We have to defend ourselves when people threaten to kill us.
