According to HRW, five young protesters were killed and many more injured.
The next day, news of the killing was spread only slowly in Jakarta.
Three weeks later, Zokovi gave a passionate speech in Jayapula, expressing deep sympathy to the families of the victims and vowing to address the historical legacy of abuse in Papua.
He said, “I hope this case will be resolved as soon as possible so that this will not happen again in the future.”
