Forty years after their Italian family founded the dynasty, two brothers fought for one of Victoria's largest real estate empires worth more than $500 million.
Colin De Lutis, a former director and developer of Carlton Football Club, lives in a mansion located in Tucla district, and three houses are located at a distance from his brother Paul. The latter brought him before the Supreme Court regarding the division of their real and business assets.
Since 2014, Paul had wanted to leave the family business, but the two brothers had a heated debate in the Supreme Court about the division of assets.
The brothers and their mother owned 38 properties worth more than $500 million that had accumulated since 1973 when the family bought Smith Street, Colin Wood.
There, the family founded Westco Jeans and gradually expanded it to 160 retail chains.
In 1999, it was sold for $85 million.
