With the recent announcement by the world’s major naval powers of plans for the construction of new types of frigates, it seems as though they were the focus of the naval forces of the great Powers overnight, starting with Japan’s decision to procure two new types of frigates in the 2018 defence budget, which has finally led to a substantial breakthrough in the Japanese frigate programme, followed by the recent announcement by Lockheed Martin of the latest plans for the United States frigate program FFG by the United States.
With the release of one of the latest frigates, the 054A, in late 2017, marking the construction of up to 29 frigates, it has approached the sum of the 053H series of frigates, and it has been 12 years since the first 054A was brought down in 2006, with the construction of such a large number of high-performance corvettes worldwide, with the exception of China, and only the “Perry” class frigates built by the United States in the 1970s and 1980s.
The reason why so many 054As have been built is simple: they are affordable, useful and additional to years of naval debt.
The 054A frigate has been favoured by the Chinese Navy for many years on the basis of high value and good combat power, with about 4,000 tons of drainage, with a 76 mm main gun, 32 units of red flags-16 and fish-8 anti-submarine launch systems, 8 eagles hitting 83 and a direct-9 helicopter, although it was built in 2006 and designed earlier, but even if it is placed in today’s condition, it can reach a moderate level among the world’s frigates.
But, after all, this is a type I ship designed at the beginning of the twenty-first century, equipped with weapons, whose power systems and electronic radar equipment are already very different from the current world-dominated frigates, as Europe’s corvettes are already equipped with full electric propulsion, small multifunctional phase-control radars, large-sized helicopter decks, and the time has come to develop a new type.
So how should China ' s new frigate develop? This is directly related to its future positioning and strategic approach to our naval forces.
The future of China’s navy will become a blue-water navy, and the future will be a seaward one, with rapid deployment in areas where China’s interests are at stake, a demonstration of the presence of force and, if necessary, a strong force to ensure that China’s vital interests in the region are not undermined.
Looking again at the positioning of new types of frigates in future Chinese naval sequences, the future Chinese navy should be similar to the United States Navy, which, in addition to the required offshore defence vessels, will form carrier battle groups or amphibious strike fleets, depending on the circumstances.
The role of the new frigate, on the other hand, should serve as the main anti-submarine force in future carrier battle groups, as well as an empty area in the center and near regions, and an amphibious attack ship strike group, requiring, on the basis of this demand, that the new frigate must have a strong anti-submarine capability and a good medium-range area clearance capability.
Based on the above positioning, it is bold to imagine the shape of a future national frigate.
First of all, there will be a significant increase in drainage compared to the current frigate type 054A, which is estimated to have about 5000-6000 tons; the power system will use an integrated power propulsion system consisting of a QC280 modified gas turbine and two diesel engines, with a maximum speed of about 30 knots and a substantial increase in continuity; With regard to the arming of the 76 mm main gun and the 1130 close defence gun, it should be retained, but a red flag 10 launch system would be added, with a 32-48 unit red flag 16 improvement and fish-8 co-mounted protraction system behind the main cannon, and a large 8-16 unit pertving system should be added to the back of the ship for the launch of the Eagle 18 and the new type of cruise missile; the hangar and parking platform would also be increased to reach the stationing and storage of two 10-ton helicopters; With regard to electronic radar systems, the high-suited radar should be equipped with a small four-sided fixed phase-control radar based on the 346A development, and the low-suited radar could be similar to the European frigate ' s multi-purpose rotation phase-control radar.
This would bring the overall level of the new frigate to its current world-class level, even in comparison to the United States FPG.
Of course, the above concept is just an assumption by the author of the new frigate of national origin, how exactly we can only wait for the new frigate to go into the water to find out, so let us all look forward to it.
